n martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":10,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":19,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":54,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":85,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":110,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born in 1205, in Shropshire, England. She married Simon de Walton - Bishop of Norwich in 1229, in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1205–":"1205–Surnud","1197–1266":"1197–1266","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1230–1283":"1230–1283","1231–1312":"1231–1312","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","10 March 1230":"10. märts 1230","1231":"1231","1230":"1230","1197":"1197","1283":"1283","1290":"1290","1228":"1228","1205":"1205","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1266":"1266","1229":"1229","1317":"1317","Stratford on Avon, Warwickshire, England":"Stratford on Avon, Warwickshire, England","Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England":"Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England","Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norwich, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, Worcestershire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1205–":"1205–Kuollut","1197–1266":"1197–1266","1228–Female":"1228–Kuollut","1230–1283":"1230–1283","1231–1312":"1231–1312","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","10 March 1230":"10. maaliskuuta 1230","1231":"1231","1230":"1230","1197":"1197","1283":"1283","1290":"1290","1228":"1228","1205":"1205","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1266":"1266","1229":"1229","1317":"1317","Stratford on Avon, Warwickshire, England":"Stratford on Avon, Warwickshire, England","Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England":"Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England","Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norwich, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shropshire, Worcest